 /
 / Content-Security-Policy whitelist for IronCart_Scan (issue #85,
 / EQP audit items 29 + 30).
 /
 / Magento_Csp merges every module's `etc/csp_whitelist.xml` into the
 / page-emitted CSP header at runtime. We declare exactly the outbound
 / hosts the module ever contacts, scoped to `connect-src` because
 / every outbound surface in this module is an XHR / cURL POST or GET —
 / no `<script src>`, no `<img src>`, no `<style>`, no iframes.
 /
 / Hosts declared here:
 /
 /   - `ironcart.dev` — covered by three opt-in flows:
 /       * IC-060 CVE proxy lookups (Check/Cve/, off-by-default; admin
 /         must enable the proxy in Stores → Configuration → Ironcart →
 /         Scan → CVE proxy)
 /       * `bin/magento ironcart:scan` with the &#45;&#45;upload flag (v3, off-by-default;
 /         admin must enable in Stores → Configuration → Ironcart →
 /         Scan → Scan Upload)
 /       * `ironcart_scan_upload_cron` cron job (v4, off-by-default;
 /         admin must enable in Stores → Configuration → Ironcart →
 /         Scan → Continuous Monitoring)
 /     All three hit `ironcart.dev` directly — same TLD, no subdomains.
 /     We declare `ironcart.dev` only; the Csp module appends scheme
 /     and trailing slash semantics per the connect-src spec.
 /
 / Notes:
 /
 /   - We deliberately do NOT whitelist the merchant's own storefront
 /     base URL (IC-080..IC-085 CSP probe pack hits it). That probe
 /     runs from the CLI / cron context, server-side cURL, never
 /     browser XHR, so it never reaches the page CSP — there is
 /     nothing to whitelist for it.
 /
 /   - The admin button's own AJAX (`view/adminhtml/web/js/run-scan-now.js`)
 /     POSTs same-origin to `ironcartscan/scans/run` and GETs to
 /     `ironcartscan/scans/status`; `'self'` is in connect-src by
 /     default so no whitelist entry is needed.
 /
 /   - No `script-src` entries: after the #85 refactor the module
 /     emits zero inline JS. All admin JS ships as RequireJS modules
 /     under `view/adminhtml/web/js/`, loaded via Magento's normal
 /     bundle pipeline, which the default 'self' / 'unsafe-inline'
 /     core CSP already covers.
 -->
<csp_whitelist xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
               xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:module:Magento_Csp:etc/csp_whitelist.xsd">
    <policies>
        <policy id="connect-src">
            <values>
                <value id="ironcart-dev" type="host">ironcart.dev</value>
            </values>
        </policy>
    </policies>
</csp_whitelist>
